{"title_page": "Sears (Mexico)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=February 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Sears Mexico <br> <span style=\"font-size:88%\">Sears Operadora M\u00e9xico, S.A. de C.V.</span>\n| logo = Sears Mexico Logo.svg\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| logo_caption = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| image_caption = \n| trading_name = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| romanized_name = \n| former_name = \n| type = [[Subsidiary]]\n| industry = [[Retail]]\n| founded = {{start date and age|1947|2|26|df=yes}} in Mexico City\n| hq_location_city = Mexico City\n| hq_location_country = Mexico\n| num_locations = 95\n| num_locations_year = 2017\n| area_served = Mexico\n| key_people = \n| products = [[Final good|Consumer goods]]\n| brands = \n| revenue = \n| revenue_year = <!-- Year of revenue data (if known) -->\n| operating_income = \n| income_year = <!-- Year of operating_income data (if known) -->\n| net_income = <!-- or: | profit = -->\n| net_income_year = <!-- or: | profit_year = --><!-- Year of net_income/profit data (if known) -->\n| assets = \n| assets_year = <!-- Year of assets data (if known) -->\n| equity = \n| equity_year = <!-- Year of equity data (if known) -->\n| owner = \n| members = \n| members_year = <!-- Year of members data (if known) -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = [[Sears]] (1947 \u2013 1997) <br> [[Grupo Sanborns]] (2007 \u2013 present)\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.sears.com.mx/}}\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n[[File:Sears Ciudad de Mexico.jpg|thumb|right|Sears store in Mexico City.]]\n\n'''Sears Operadora M\u00e9xico, S.A. de C.V.''' is a [[department store]] chain located in [[Mexico]], operating more than 95 stores all over Mexico. Sears M\u00e9xico is operated by [[Grupo Carso]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thespinfactor.com/thetruth/2009/04/20/sears-en-mexico-contrata-a-los-retrasados-mentales-o-los-vuelve/ |title=Sears en M\u00e9xico contrata a los retrasados mentales, o los vuelve\u2026 |language=Spanish |access-date=2019-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091109154121/http://thespinfactor.com/thetruth/2009/04/20/sears-en-mexico-contrata-a-los-retrasados-mentales-o-los-vuelve/ |archive-date=2009-11-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n=== Early History ===\nOn 26 February 1947, the first Sears in Mexico was opened in [[Mexico City]] by [[Sears|Sears, Roebuck and Co.]] to an excited public. In the first three days of operation around 110,000 guests visited the store spending around $600,000 on goods. In its first week of operation, the store struggled to stock its shelves, requiring three airplanes to fly in more goods from a Texas warehouse owned by the parent company. Its introduction to the Mexican economy is seen by some as helping to usher in a consumer evolution in Mexico, shifting the nation's focus from nationalism and redistribution of wealth to happiness and individual self-realization.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Moreno |first1=Julio E. |date=December 2000 |title=Marketing in Mexico: Sears, Roebuck Company, J. Walter Thompson, and the Culture of North American Commerce in Mexico City during the 1940s |journal=Enterprise & Society |volume=1 |issue=4 |pages=683\u2013692 |jstor=23699530 |doi=10.1093/es/1.4.683 }}</ref><ref name=\"History\">{{cite web |url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/sears-roebuck-de-m%C3%A9xico-s-a-de-c-v-history/ |title=Sears Roebuck de M\u00e9xico, S.A. de C.V. History |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=n.d. |website=Finding Universe |publisher=Finding Universe |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn its first year of operation, the Mexico City store did around $16 million in business, almost twice as much as was expected by its parent company. However, just a few months after opening, in order to prevent a drain on the nation's foreign-currency reserves, Mexico barred some nonessential imports and raised tariffs on others. This impacted the Mexico City store tremendously, which was at the time importing around 90 percent of its merchandise.<ref name=\"History\"/>\n\nThis forced the store to create alliances with Mexican manufacturers, offering financial and technical aid to suppliers to meet its burgeoning demand for goods. It also bought interest in factories that were producing its merchandise. By 1949, Sears Mexico had around 2,500 Mexican suppliers furnishing some 80 percent of the goods in the Mexico City store.<ref name=\"History\"/>\n\nA second and third Sears were opened in 1949 in Monterrey and Guadalajara, and by 1953 Sears had seven stores in Mexico and annual sales of more than $15 million and employed around 1,900 people. These employees received unheard of benefits from the company including: overtime, merit raises, cost-of-living allowances, paid vacations, retirement funds, access to company cafeterias, free medical treatment and medicines and discounts on purchases.<ref name=\"History\"/>\n\nBy 1956 there were 17 Sears stores in Mexico with a sales volume of around $25 million. There were around 3,200 employees at that time, all but 16 of which were Mexican citizens. Additionally, about 90 percent of the merchandise sold in its stores was made in Mexico.<ref name=\"History\"/>\n\n=== Grupo Carso ===\nOn April 2, 1997, [[Sears]] formed a strategic alliance with [[Grupo Carso]], owned by Mexican businessman [[Carlos Slim Hel\u00fa]], through which Sears agreed to sell 85% of its share of Sears Mexico to Grupo Carso, until 1997.  As of 2007, Grupo Carso owned a 100% share of the company. Even though Sears unveiled a new lowercase logo in the [[United States]] in 2010, Sears Mexico changed its logo to a red variant of the standard Sears blue logo in 2013.\n\nDespite the bankruptcy of its former parent company, the closing of many stores in the United States and Canada, and subsequent sale to [[ESL Investments]], Sears Mexico still remains open for business due to different ownership.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.sears.com.mx Official website]\n\n{{Sears Holdings Corporation}}\n\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1947]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Mexico City]]\n[[Category:Retail companies of Mexico]]\n[[Category:Department stores of Mexico]]\n[[Category:Sears Holdings]]\n[[Category:1947 establishments in Mexico]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=February 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Sears Mexico <br> <span style=\"font-size:88%\">Sears Operadora M\u00e9xico, S.A. de C.V.</span>\n| logo = Sears Mexico Logo.svg\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| logo_caption = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| image_caption = \n| trading_name = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| romanized_name = \n| former_name = \n| type = [[Subsidiary]]\n| industry = [[Retail]]\n| founded = {{start date and age|1947|2|26|df=yes}} in Mexico City\n| hq_location_city = Mexico City\n| hq_location_country = Mexico\n| num_locations = 95\n| num_locations_year = 2017\n| area_served = Mexico\n| key_people = \n| products = [[Final good|Consumer goods]]\n| brands = \n| revenue = \n| revenue_year = <!-- Year of revenue data (if known) -->\n| operating_income = \n| income_year = <!-- Year of operating_income data (if known) -->\n| net_income = <!-- or: | profit = -->\n| net_income_year = <!-- or: | profit_year = --><!-- Year of net_income/profit data (if known) -->\n| assets = \n| assets_year = <!-- Year of assets data (if known) -->\n| equity = \n| equity_year = <!-- Year of equity data (if known) -->\n| owner = \n| members = \n| members_year = <!-- Year of members data (if known) -->\n| num_employees = \n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = [[Sears]] (1947 \u2013 1997) <br> [[Grupo Sanborns]] (2007 \u2013 present)\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.sears.com.mx/}}\n| footnotes =